<paragraph id="8B8D36E5A6414A12FF2FFC0132FEFC37" blockId="47.[151,466,979,1006]" box="[151,466,979,1006]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<heading id="D0C58189A6414A12FF2FFC0132FEFC37" bold="true" box="[151,466,979,1006]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B946EAF7A6414A12FF2FFC0132FEFC37" bold="true" box="[151,466,979,1006]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<taxonomicName id="4C324D66A6414A12FF2FFC013252FC34" authorityName="Li &amp; Sattler" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[151,382,980,1006]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Mesophleps" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geodes">
<emphasis id="B946EAF7A6414A12FF2FFC013252FC34" bold="true" box="[151,382,980,1006]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Mesophleps geodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8D36E5A6414A12FF2FFBCF323BFB36" blockId="47.[151,1436,1050,1765]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Labial palpus segment 2 broadly triangular, 3 upturned at right angles or porrect and obscured in 2. Forewing with moderate pterostigma basad of R 
<subScript id="17B634A0A6414A12FDB2FB9B313EFB86" attach="left" box="[522,530,1102,1116]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">1</subScript>
, R 
<subScript id="17B634A0A6414A12FD8AFB9B3116FB86" attach="left" box="[562,570,1102,1116]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">3</subScript>
approximated to common stalk of R 
<subScript id="17B634A0A6414A12FC6EFB9B30C2FB86" attach="left" box="[982,1006,1102,1116]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">4+5</subScript>
+M 
<subScript id="17B634A0A6414A12FBAFFB9B3733FB86" attach="right" box="[1047,1055,1102,1116]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">1</subScript>
, M 
<subScript id="17B634A0A6414A12FBFDFB9B3761FB86" attach="left" box="[1093,1101,1102,1116]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">3</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript id="17B634A0A6414A12FB01FB9B37EDFB86" attach="left" box="[1209,1217,1102,1116]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">1</subScript>
connate or stalked; hind wing with R 
<subScript id="17B634A0A6414A12FEE6FBA1324AFB58" attach="left" box="[350,358,1140,1154]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">1</subScript>
present, anastomosed with Sc near base of wing, Rs+M 
<subScript id="17B634A0A6414A12FC5FFBA130C3FB58" attach="left" box="[999,1007,1140,1154]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">1</subScript>
on long common stalk, M 
<subScript id="17B634A0A6414A12FAA6FBA1360AFB58" attach="left" box="[1310,1318,1140,1154]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">3</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript id="17B634A0A6414A12FA2CFBA136B0FB58" attach="left" box="[1428,1436,1140,1154]" fontSize="6" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">1</subScript>
approximated at base. Forewing uniformly dark brown, unmarked, or grey with more or less distinct markings. Pregenital abdomen with TIV–VIII (in female TIV–VII) with very broad, medially indented band of microtrichia (
<figureCitation id="13092A60A6414A12FAD2FB653399FB36" captionStart="FIGURES 11–16" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1904,1927]" captionTargetBox="[217,1354,229,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-93@12.[202,1389,214,1889]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 11–16. Morphology of Mesophleps spp. 11. abdominal sternal support system of M. epiochra (Meyrick), ♂, slide no. 664a, Sattler; 12. ovipositor of M. tephrastis-group, lateral view; 13. 'signum' of M. tephrastis (Meyrick), slide no. 30947; 14. SVIII of M. bifidella sp. nov. holotype, ♂, slide no. 463c, Sattler; 15. SVIII of M. gigantella sp. nov., paratype, ♂, slide no. 30934; 16. SVIII of M. geodes (Meyrick), ♂, slide no. 30939." pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Figs 16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13092A60A6414A12FF79FB013227FB36" box="[193,267,1236,1260]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–22" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1952,1975]" captionTargetBox="[198,1404,207,1940]" captionTargetId="figure-78@13.[179,1423,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 17–22. Abdomens of Mesophleps spp. 17. M. safranella (Legrand), ♀, slide no. 30970; 18. M. epiochra (Meyrick), ♂, slide no. 15833; 19. M. geodes (Meyrick), ♂, slide no. 30939; 20. M. geodes (Meyrick), ♀, slide no. 30937; 21. M. catericta (Meyrick), ♂, slide no. 30972; 22. M. tephrastis (Meyrick), ♀, slide no. 30947." pageId="47" pageNumber="48">19–20</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C328656EA6414A12FF71FB223049FA1E" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8D36E5A6414A12FF71FB22308BFA82" blockId="47.[151,1436,1050,1765]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="B946EAF7A6414A12FF71FB22321BFACA" bold="true" box="[201,311,1271,1296]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Genitalia</emphasis>
<materialsCitation id="3B5A3CB8A6414A12FEF8FB22308FFA82" location="Uncus" municipality="Phallus straight" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" specimenCount="1" specimenCount-male="1">
<specimenCount id="9D34FD6CA6414A12FEF8FB22327FFAD0" box="[320,339,1271,1290]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
(
<figureCitation id="13092A60A6414A12FEDAFB2D3296FACA" box="[354,442,1272,1296]" captionStart="FIGURES 78–82" captionStartId="72.[151,264,1928,1951]" captionTargetBox="[190,1400,188,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-71@72.[182,1406,169,1897]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="FIGURES 78–82. Male genitalia of Mesophleps spp. 78. M. parvella sp. nov. paratype, slide no. 30915; 79. M. aspina sp. nov. holotype, slide no. 30960; 80. M. truncatella sp. nov. holotype, slide no. 30889; 81. M. undulatella sp. nov. holotype, slide no. 30966; 82. M. geodes (Meyrick), slide no. 30939." pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Figs 82</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13092A60A6414A12FE7FFB2D32CAFACA" box="[455,486,1272,1296]" captionStart="FIGURES 83–88" captionStartId="73.[151,264,1951,1974]" captionTargetBox="[204,1386,194,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-71@73.[181,1405,181,1930]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURES 83–88. Male genitalia of Mesophleps spp., genus? and Sarotorna. 83. M. catericta (Meyrick), slide no. 30972; 84. M. tetrachroa (Lower), slide no. 30945; 85. M. tephrastis (Meyrick), slide no. 30948; 86. M. chloranthes (Lower), slide no. 30968; 87.? mesophracta (Turner), slide no. 30958; 88. Sarotorna mesoleuca (Lower), slide no. 11620, ANIC." pageId="47" pageNumber="48">83</figureCitation>
). 
<location id="8EED603EA6414A12FE44FB2C3168FACA" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:039B87F3A6414A12FF2FFC013759F93E:8EED603EA6414A12FE44FB2C3168FACA" box="[508,580,1273,1296]" municipality="Phallus straight" name="Uncus" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Uncus</location>
sub-rectangular or distally rounded and medially constricted; gnathos arms medially fused to single hook, valva simple. 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BE9AC9FA6414A12FD1FFAC93077FAEE" box="[679,859,1308,1332]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Phallus straight</collectingMunicipality>
, with moderately swollen base, evenly tapered to sharp point or angled in middle with abruptly narrowed distal portion
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8D36E5A6414A12FF71FAB13049FA1E" blockId="47.[151,1436,1050,1765]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="B946EAF7A6414A12FF71FAB13214FAA7" bold="true" box="[201,312,1380,1405]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Genitalia</emphasis>
º (
<figureCitation id="13092A60A6414A12FEDCFAB1312EFAA6" box="[356,514,1380,1404]" captionStart="FIGURES 106–111" captionStartId="77.[151,264,1926,1949]" captionTargetBox="[209,1358,192,1880]" captionTargetId="figure-75@77.[181,1405,177,1905]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURES 106–111. Female genitalia of Mesophleps spp. 106. M. nairobiensis Li &amp; Zheng, slide no. 30825; 107. M. coffeae sp. nov. paratype, slide no. 30796; 108. M. truncatella sp. nov. paratype, slide no. 30891; 109. M. undulatella sp. nov. paratype, slide no. 30965; 110. M. geodes (Meyrick), slide no. 30937; 111. M. catericta (Meyrick), slide no. 30973." pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Figs 110, 111</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13092A60A6414A12FDA8FAB13154FAA6" box="[528,632,1380,1404]" captionStart="FIGURES 131–142" captionStartId="80.[151,264,1833,1856]" captionTargetBox="[196,1376,213,1766]" captionTargetId="figure-127@80.[181,1405,193,1813]" captionTargetPageId="80" captionText="FIGURES 131–142. Female segment VIII of Mesophleps spp. 131. M. ochracella (Turati), slide no. 30982; 132. M. unguella sp. nov. paratype, slide no. 30956; 133. M. gigantella sp. nov. paratype, slide no. 15836; 134. M. sp. (Yunnan), slide no. L95070; 135. M. albilinella (Park), slide no. L03077; 136. M. nairobiensis Li &amp; Zheng, slide no. 30825; 137. M. coffeae sp. nov. paratype, slide no. 30796; 138. M. parvella sp. nov. paratype, slide no. 30951; 139. M. truncatella sp. nov. paratype, slide no. 30891; 140. M. undulatella sp. nov. paratype, slide no. 30965; 141. M. geodes (Meyrick), slide no. 30937; 142. M. catericta (Meyrick), slide no. 30973." pageId="47" pageNumber="48">141, 142</figureCitation>
). Papillae anales sub-rectangular, width about three-times length, apophyses posteriores less than twice length of apophyses anteriores. Ostium bursae membranous; ductus bursae of moderate length; ductus seminalis from ductus or cervix bursae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C328656EA6414A12FF71FA053776F946" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8D36E5A6414A12FF71FA0536B8F9EA" blockId="47.[151,1436,1050,1765]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="B946EAF7A6414A12FF71FA053217FA32" bold="true" box="[201,315,1488,1512]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
Despite several specializations such as the unusual genitalia we believe that 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D66A6414A12FB2EFA0537CEFA32" authorityName="Li &amp; Sattler" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[1174,1250,1488,1512]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Mesophleps" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geodes">
<emphasis id="B946EAF7A6414A12FB2EFA0537CEFA32" box="[1174,1250,1488,1512]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">geodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is merely a specialized member of the same clade and consequently synonymize the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D66A6414A12FC6EFA213795F9D6" authority="Meyrick" authorityName="Meyrick" authorityYear="1929" box="[982,1209,1524,1548]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Bucolarcha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B946EAF7A6414A12FC6EFA213779F9D6" box="[982,1109,1524,1548]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Bucolarcha</emphasis>
Meyrick
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D66A6414A12FB4FFA213656F9D6" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1825" box="[1271,1402,1524,1548]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Mesophleps" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B946EAF7A6414A12FB4FFA213656F9D6" box="[1271,1402,1524,1548]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Mesophleps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on account of the abdominal bands of microtrichia, and the larval biology (seed feeder in the pods of leguminous trees).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8D36E5A6414A12FF71F9E93776F946" blockId="47.[151,1436,1050,1765]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
The two species placed in this group differ from each other in many characters but are tentatively placed together because they uniquely share the broad band of microtrichia on abdominal TVIII of the male (elsewhere in 
<taxonomicName id="4C324D66A6414A12FF2FF9513231F946" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1825" box="[151,285,1668,1692]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Mesophleps" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B946EAF7A6414A12FF2FF9513231F946" box="[151,285,1668,1692]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Mesophleps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only on TIV–VII) and, in the female, the unusually broad papillae anales.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C328656EA6414A12FF71F972303CF91A" box="[201,784,1703,1728]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B8D36E5A6414A12FF71F972303CF91A" blockId="47.[151,1436,1050,1765]" box="[201,784,1703,1728]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="B946EAF7A6414A12FF71F9723204F91A" bold="true" box="[201,296,1703,1728]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" reason="1">Biology.</emphasis>
